Drafted Recipe 5.10 (Deceased Patient Resolution and Record Reconciliation) at [38;5;10mchapter05.10-deceased-patient-resolution-reconciliation.md[0m. The recipe covers:[0m[0m
[0m[0m
- **The Problem**: Multi-scenario opening grounded in the Tuesday-morning chemo-reminder-to-the-deceased experience, expanding through nine real-world institutional scenarios from MPI operators to SSA itself to family-side experience.[0m[0m
- **The Technology**: Why "deceased flag plus date" is incomplete, the multi-source landscape (SSA DMF, state vital-records, payer feeds, EHR, hospice, family-reported, obituaries, claims-cessation inferences, provider-reported), and the nine-dimensional reconciliation problem.[0m[0m
- **General Architecture Pattern**: Six-stage pipeline (ingest, match, multi-source-reconcile, MPI-update-atomic, downstream-cascade, cross-cutting concerns) with ASCII flow diagram.[0m[0m
- **AWS Implementation**: S3 landing zone, Glue normalization, Step Functions orchestration, Lambda per-stage handlers, DynamoDB death-event log, Aurora MPI, EventBridge fan-out, full prerequisites table, ingredients, six pseudocode steps with detailed inline reasoning, sample JSON outputs, performance benchmarks, and failure-mode list.[0m[0m
- **Why This Isn't Production-Ready**: Per-source onboarding, family-intake discipline, premature-death-report reversal pathway, posthumous-protection access-control engine, personal-representative workflow, three review queues, cross-recipe coordination, idempotency, quality-drift monitoring, ownership.[0m[0m
- **Honest Take, Variations (12), Related Recipes, Resources, Implementation Time tiers, Tags, Navigation.**[0m[0m
